==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skimmington
<hw>Skim"ming*ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain. Perhaps the name of some notorius scold.]</ety> <def>A word
employed in the phrase, <xex>To ride Skimmington</xex>; that is to ride
on a horse with a woman, but behind her, facing backward, carrying a
distaff, and accompanied by a procession of jeering neighbors making
mock music; a cavalcade in ridicule of a henpecked man. The custom was
in vogue in parts of England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skimp</ent>⟦br⟧
